oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Evins Brothers Store
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of several people gathered outside of the Evins Brothers Store and other establishments in Culleoka, Tennessee. A group of horses with a wagon can be seen by a tree (center). The shop was originally known as the Howlett General Store until the Evins brothers purchased it in 1893. Writing on the bottom of the photograph reads "Evins Bro's Store Main St. / Culleoka, Tenn."
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: People; Stores & shops; Carts & wagons; Horses
